-- Innodis of Mauritius Full-Year Net Income Advances 10% as Revenue Climbs
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2010-09-28T06:46:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/innodis-of-mauritius-full-year-net-income-advances-10-as-revenue-climbs.html
Innodis Ltd. , a Mauritian food
manufacturer, said full-year profit climbed 10 percent as
revenue increased.  Net income grew to 133.1 million rupees ($4.36 million) in
the 12 months through June, from 120.6 million rupees a year
earlier, the Port Louis-based company said in a statement
published in l’Express newspaper today. Sales advanced 1.4
percent to 2.8 billion rupees, it said.  “All our business units performed better due to improved
marketing efforts and consistent quality of our products,” the
company said. “Regionally, our  Mozambique  operations have
experienced a positive turnaround.”  Innodis declared a dividend of 1.4 rupees a share, compared
with 1.2 rupees a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Kamlesh Bhuckory  in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 